long.ar:
The extension manager is one of your best choices for Chrome extension management, providing you with an efficient way. It has a simple interface and simplified usage process, helping you toggle the status of extensions between enabled and disabled. Moreover, Extension Manger for Chrome‚Ñ¢ provides the function to support you to customize the creation of Chrome extension groups for different usage scenarios.
  üöÄ Feature:
  ‚öô One-click to switch status between enabled and disabled.
  ‚öô One-click to uninstall Chrome extension.
  ‚öô Supports custom grouping and provides operations such as add, delete, and edit.
  ‚öô Supports search keywords to quickly locate Chrome extensions;
  ‚öô Supports filtering to quickly view enabled and disabled extensions.
  ‚öô Minimum permission requests for safe use.
